# ── Mirror publication allowlist — gate G1 (spec 07 §8.4, SC-6) ──────────────
#
# Glob patterns of the ONLY paths permitted in the public mirror
# (github.com/keel-trade/keel-trade). On EVERY sync — tag push and manual
# dispatch alike — every file in the staged public tree (excluding the
# checkout's own .git/) must match at least one pattern below. Any unmatched
# file turns the sync red BEFORE anything is pushed. Fail-closed: this
# manifest inverts the trust direction — the rsync exclude list is a first
# filter; this file is the boundary.
#
# Adding a new public file class REQUIRES a same-PR edit here — loud by
# construction.
#
# Semantics: Python fnmatch globs, case-sensitive, matched against
# posix paths relative to the staged-tree root by
# .github/scripts/mirror_gates.py. NOTE: fnmatch `*` matches across `/`,
# so `keel/*.py` covers every .py file nested anywhere under keel/.
#
# This file is intentionally published (self-allowlisted, first entry): it
# names only public paths, and publishing it makes the publication boundary
# third-party-auditable.
.mirror-allowlist
.mirror-import-denylist
# ── Repo meta (public-overlay + SDK root) ────────────────────────────────────
.gitignore
.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/config.yml
.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/*.md
AGENTS.md
CHANGELOG.md
CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
CONTRIBUTING.md
LICENSE
README.md
glama.json
pyproject.toml
# ── SDK package code + bundled data ──────────────────────────────────────────
keel/*.py
keel/data/*.json
keel/data/knowledge/*.md
keel/data/patterns/*.md
keel/data/reference/*.md
keel/skills/*.md
pipeline_engine/*.py
scripts/*.py
scripts/icon.png
scripts/manifest.template.json
tests/*.py
